## Layout System

This project uses **two different grid systems** depending on layout complexity needs.

### Simple Grid (Default - Use This)

**Location:** `TwoColumnLayout.module.css`

**What it is:** A straightforward CSS Grid with `grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr` that creates two equal columns on desktop and stacks on mobile.

**Usage:**
```typescript
import layoutStyles from './TwoColumnLayout.module.css'

<section className={`${styles.mySection} ${layoutStyles.container}`}>
  <div>Left column</div>
  <div>Right column</div>
</section>
```

**When to use:**
- Standard two-column layouts (most sections)
- Even splits (50/50)
- Simple content arrangement
- Default choice for new sections

**Currently used in:**
- Leading Section (image + text)
- Stop Doing Start Being section
- Most content sections

---

### Fluid Grid (Advanced - Use Sparingly)

**Location:** `styles/fluid-grid.css`

**What it is:** A 24-column CSS Grid system (8 columns on mobile) that allows precise positioning using grid coordinates. Inspired by modern editorial design systems.

**Usage:**
```typescript
<div className="fluid-engine">
  <div 
    className="grid-block"
    style={{
      '--mobile-grid-area': '1/2/9/10',
      '--desktop-grid-area': '1/2/23/14',
    } as React.CSSProperties}
  >
    Content here
  </div>
</div>
```

**When to use:**
- Complex layouts with overlapping elements
- Asymmetric columns (60/40, 37.5/50 instead of 50/50)
- Precise positioning with grid coordinates (e.g., "start at column 15, end at 24")
- Creative, magazine-style layouts
- Elements that need z-index layering

**Examples available in:** `examples/LeadingSection-with-fluid-grid.example.tsx`

**Documentation:** 
- `README-FLUID-GRID.md` - Complete guide
- `VISUAL-GRID-GUIDE.md` - ASCII diagrams showing the grid
- `grid-system-analysis.md` - Technical details

---

### Grid Comparison

| Feature | Simple Grid | Fluid Grid |
|---------|-------------|------------|
| Complexity | Low | Medium |
| Column control | 2 columns (50/50) | 24 columns (any ratio) |
| Positioning | Automatic | Precise (row/col coordinates) |
| Learning curve | Minimal | Requires understanding grid-area |
| Best for | Standard layouts | Complex, creative layouts |
| Maintenance | Easy | More complex |
| **Use when** | **Most of the time** | Only when needed |

**Default choice:** Stick with simple grid (`TwoColumnLayout.module.css`) unless complexity requires fluid grid.

