## What NOT to Do

### ❌ Don't Change the Voice
- Don't make text more "professional" or corporate
- Don't remove vulnerability or directness
- Don't add buzzwords or generic phrasing
- Don't dilute the specific examples

### ❌ Don't Over-Engineer
- Don't add state management libraries (Redux, Zustand, etc.)
- Don't add CSS frameworks (Tailwind, Bootstrap, etc.)
- Don't add unnecessary dependencies
- Don't create complex abstractions for simple problems

### ❌ Don't Optimize for Everyone
- Don't water down the content to appeal to more people
- Don't remove "controversial" stances (values-driven, consensus-building, etc.)
- Don't make it generic or safe
- The site SHOULD filter for fit

### ❌ Don't Break Accessibility
- Don't use color alone to convey meaning
- Don't forget alt text on images
- Don't make touch targets too small
- Don't prevent keyboard navigation

